entities.trees

Class TDP_Subtree_Solution

  • java.lang.Object
    • entities.trees.TDP_Solution
      • entities.trees.TDP_Subtree_Solution
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<TDP_Subtree_Solution>

    public class TDP_Subtree_Solution
extends TDP_Solution
implements Comparable<TDP_Subtree_Solution>
    A subtree representation of T-DP solutions that allows for sharing common subtrees. Each subtree solution consists of one decision and a collection of other subtree solutions from the target state (one for each child in the stage tree).
    Author:
    Nikolaos Tziavelis
    See Also:
    TDP_Recursive

    • Field Detail

      • parent_decision

        private TDP_Decision parent_decision
        The first decision contained in the solution. It leads to a node from which the other subtrees start.

      • subtrees

        private TDP_Subtree_Collection subtrees
        A collection of subtree solutions starting from the target of parent_decision. This collection of subtrees is stored with a "shared prefix" structure.
        See Also:
        TDP_Subtree_Collection

      • last_sidetrack

        public int last_sidetrack
        Used by TDP_Recursive. Since that algorithm uses the Lawler procedure on the possible subtrees, every time we want to take the successors of a solution, we need to remember from which stage to start. It is equal to the index of the last solution of the prefix (before we expand it).

      • next

        public TDP_Subtree_Solution next
        Used by TDP_Recursive. A next pointer points to the next best subtree that has the same origin.
